Detailed Description

cvmx_l2c_cbc::_rsderr

This register records error information for all CBC RSD errors. An error locks the INDEX and [SYN] and sets the bit corresponding to the error received. RSDDBE errors take priority and overwrite an earlier logged RSDSBE error. Only one of [RSDSBE]/[RSDDBE] is set at any given time and serves to document which error the INDEX/[SYN] is associated with. The syndrome is recorded for DBE errors, though the utility of the value is not clear.
